<h2 style="text-align: center;">THE INTERNATIONAL OLYMPIAD IN INFORMATICS</h2>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">The 32<sup>nd</sup> <a href="https://ioinformatics.org/">International Olympiad in Informatics</a> (IOI 2020) has been held from 13 to 19 September 2020. It is the most prestigious computer science competition for secondary school and high school students around the world. The competition is one of five international science Olympiads held annually. IOI 2020 is hosted by the <a href="http://www.nus.edu.sg/">National University of Singapore</a> (NUS) <a href="https://www.comp.nus.edu.sg/">School of Computing</a>. The competition is powered by <a href="https://www.acer.com/worldwide/">Acer</a> and supported by the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/">Ministry of Education</a> (MOE) Singapore and the <a href="https://www.visitsingapore.com/mice/en/about-us/about-secb/">Singapore Exhibition &amp; Convention Bureau</a> (SECB).</div>
</div>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">
